<div class="lightblock">
== — Description — ==
<center>The '''Reality Magnet''' is designated as the '''88<sup>th</sup>''' entity of the '''Backrooms'''.</center><br>
{{Blurimage|caption=<code>Fig 1.</code> A witness's sketch of the '''Reality Magnet'''.|file=Entity X captured .png}}
'''Entity 88''', otherwise formally nicknamed as the '''Reality Magnet''', is mostly known for its ability to forcefully pull and, thus, extract structural parts within its vicinity, and can seldom warp time of its surrounding. Because of this capability, crumbled sections of walls, destroyed light fixtures, and unrecognizable furnitures are constantly shielding the entity, which also effectively makes it impossible to identify its true, naked appearance. However, this swirling shield does not only consist of cold concrete and metal, as the entity roams through a level, it forcefully drags the remains of its previous victims into its orbit. The bodies of unfortunate wanderers are instantly crushed upon impact, their bones snapped and fused into the rotating mass of debris. Shredded clothing, dried blood, and mangled limbs can often be seen mangled and mixed between the broken bricks. It is, as of yet, inexplicable how the entity possess such form of gravitational pull, but the gruesome sight of human remains spinning alongside a sphere of shattered walls makes it one of the most terrifying phenomena in the Backrooms.

</div>
<div class="lightblock">
== — Behaviors — ==
{{Blurimage|caption=<code>Fig 2.</code> An image depicting the destruction '''Entity 88'''' has inflicted to a house in [[Level 9]].|file=Magnet Aftermath.png}}
'''Entity 88''' is highly hostile. The moment any living being or another entity catches its attention, it attacks immediately. It does not stalk targets like a biological predator; instead, it drifts swiftly towards its selected prey, and breaks through obstacles in its path without halt. The primary hazard is its unpredictable magnetic force. If a wanderer gets adequately close to its field, said pull starts to take effect, which forcefully pulls all metallic items the wanderer have. Heavy backpacks, flashlights, and zippers on clothing will tear away and fly into the entity's debris aura. The entity rotates the sharp wall pieces and broken furniture akin to a mechanical saw. It rams these heavy materials directly into trapped wanderers, which causes serious internal trauma and lethal damage. Ecaping its pulling field is nearly impossible, therefore, the only reliable method of survival is early detection. If a wanderer notices loose nails floating in the air, or hears continous, rumbling sound, one must retreat immediately.

{{Blurimage|caption=<code>Fig 3.</code> An image displaying what the '''Reality Magnet''' can do to an electrical device; a computer.|file=Melting Computer.png}}

Alongside the physical pull, the entity carries a strange electronic distortion field that appears as flashing binary numbers. This field is capable of completely disrupting any technology or computers nearby. The moment '''Entity 88''' gets close to a computer, the processor is forced into a non-stop loop, and the CPU overheats almost instantly. Within a few seconds, the intense heat melts the motherboard and causes the device to catch aflame from the inside out. This completely breaks all radios, cameras, and data gear, making it impossible to capture a close-up image of the entity.

In few deeper, and patient observations, it has been proven '''Entity 88''' can divide itself into two selves akin to how microscopic cells reproduce. It is apparently unpredictable when one will split, however it is strongly believed only one of its divided two can divide again. Because of this mean of reproductive process that the entity possesses, its general population has been growing since its date of birth, concerning and forcing researchers to operate a method on neutralizing this entity, albeit no plausible method has been thought of yet.

</div>
<div class="lightblock">
== — History — ==
It has been confirmed the [[Architect Industries]] and the [[A.D.F.]] actually made this anomaly by accident back in 2012. They discovered a peculiar area in [[Level 3]] where metal objects were floating midair. Their flashlights stop functioning when they entered said zone, so they built a small outpost beside it for research. They brought in and attached heavy electricity generators to the flashlights and other devices to force them to function normally. That was a mistake.

During an experiment, the generators overloaded. The machines did not solely explode; they started pulling in almost everything in its vicinity. Three [[A.D.F.]] researchers were standing too close, thus, their skin and bones were aggressively ripped right off their bodies, mixing them up with the melting metal and broken concrete blocks. All of that debris and flesh fused together into a giant, violent, and uneven sphere. The [[A.D.F.]] tried to block the path to the zone, but the entity smashed through the heavy steel gates. It has been wandering around the level ever since, gaining size, violence, and spreading through other levels gradually.
</div>
<div class="lightblock">
== — Habitat — ==
'''Entity 88''' is primarily found in levels with abundance of metal, and machinaries, however, perhaps fortunately, sighting this entity is considerably rare. Levels that are documented to house this entity include:
* [[Level 3]]
* Boiler Room of [[Level 5]]
* [[Level 9]]
* [[Level 14]]
* [[Level 15]]
* [[Level 17]]
* And many other more. If you encounter '''Entity 88''' in an unlisted level, it is highly encouraged add the level to this list.

</div><div class="lightblock">
== — Survival Tips — ==

* Hide immediately: The moment you notice the entity is nearby, find a place to hide and do NOT move.

* Avoid magnetic metals: Travel with as little metal as possible. Never hide inside lockers or cabinets made of iron, cobalt, or nickel, as the magnetic pull will crush the structure with you inside.

* Seek wooden shelter: If you need cover quickly, hide under a standard wooden table or any furniture that does not contain metal components.

* Use fire with caution: Open flames can scare the entity away for a short time. However, attempting to fight it with fire is highly dangerous and not recommended.

* React to audio cues: If you hear a heavy rumbling sound or notice loose metal shaking, do not hesitate. Retreat immediately or drop out of sight.
</div>
